.TH "spi_split_transfers_maxsize" 9 "spi_split_transfers_maxsize" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
spi_split_transfers_maxsize \- split spi transfers into multiple transfers when an individual transfer exceeds a certain size
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" spi_split_transfers_maxsize
.BI "(struct spi_controller *ctlr "  ","
.BI "struct spi_message *msg "  ","
.BI "size_t maxsize "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctlr" 12
the \fIspi_controller\fP for this transfer
.IP "msg" 12
the \fIspi_message\fP to transform
.IP "maxsize" 12
the maximum when to apply this
.IP "gfp" 12
GFP allocation flags
.SH "RETURN"
status of transformation
